706591f-a.text:
725 St. Mark's Ave., north side, between Nostrand and New York Avus., showing the home of the late Eugene G. Blackford, who at one time was State Commissioner of fish hatcheries, and New York's largest wholesale fish
merchant.
May 29, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
